solution: class Solution {
    public int minDays(int n) {
        return dfs(n, new HashMap<>());
    }

    private int dfs(int n, Map<Integer, Integer> memo) {
        if (n <= 1) return n;
        if (memo.containsKey(n)) return memo.get(n);
        int res = 1 + Math.min(
            n % 2 + dfs(n / 2, memo),
            n % 3 + dfs(n / 3, memo)
        );
        memo.put(n, res);
        return res;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(log n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses memoized DFS with pruning: instead of simulating every possible path, it greedily chooses between the optimal divide-by-2 or divide-by-3 moves, adding the remainder as single-day steps. This reduces the state space to logarithmic depth, making it feasible for n up to 2 billion.

